  "title": "Growing Chickpea at ICRISAT Center as a Rainy-season Crop",
  "abstract": "As chickpea is usually grown on residual moislure and often without irrigation, drought is commonly regarded the crop's foremost abiotic stress factor. Assuming irrigation water is not available, there seem to be three ways to tackle the drought problem for chickpea.",
